From 381aca79440f139fc2629cd6670dce283573a7ec Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 07:30:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: switch AI pipeline to tool use (Claude Code style) with
 client-side auto-placement

- Replace schema-in-prompt + forced JSON generation with proper tool use API
  - New shared/schema/buildToolDefinitions.ts converts each AgentAction schema
    into a Vercel AI SDK tool() definition (action name = tool name, _type stripped
    from params and re-added by server before emitting SSE)
  - server/AgentService.ts: uses streamText() with tools + maxSteps:20, enables
    Anthropic extended thinking, processes fullStream tool-call events instead of
    incrementally parsing JSON text; removes fake assistant prefix hack
  - server/prompt/buildSystemPrompt.ts: defaults withSchema to false (tools replace it)
  - server/prompt/sections/intro-section.ts: rewords from "respond with JSON" to
    "call the provided tools"
  - server/prompt/sections/rules-section.ts: replaces JSON schema rules with tool
    use rules; adds auto-placement note; removes coordinate tips
  - backend/llm_service.py: switches to litellm tool use API (tools/tool_choice params,
    tool_call delta accumulation, emits complete actions on finish_reason=tool_calls)

- AI decides WHAT to create; client handles WHERE (auto-placement)
  - shared/format/FocusedShape.ts: x/y optional on all shape types
  - shared/schema/AgentActionSchemas.ts: x/y optional on EquationAction
  - New client/actions/computeAutoPlacement.ts: places new shapes near context items,
    then selected shapes, then viewport centre
  - client/actions/CreateActionUtil.ts: injects auto-placement when x/y absent
  - client/actions/EquationActionUtil.ts: uses auto-placement when x/y absent

Wire format to frontend (SSE data: {action}\n\n) is unchanged.

